<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n50091b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n50" href="#n50091b">N50 (VI.B.37)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n50all.htm#n50091b"> 91(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the burden (Hosty)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The old ballad, in its characteristic form, belongs peculiarly to the countries of Scandinavia; and it is very remarkable that the corresponding English <mark>ballads</mark>, which often, both in their prevailing tone and in their form&mdash;as, for instance, with regard to <mark>the burthen</mark>&mdash;betray a surprising similarity with the Scandinavian, are in England found exclusively in the north. <small> J.J.A. Worsaae, <a name="JJAW2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JJAW2"><cite title="source">An Account of the Danes and Norwegians in England, Scotland and Ireland</cite></a> (1852) 89</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
